dct_title_s: An accurate map of all his Majesty's dominions in Germany, with the adjacent countries
dct_description_sm: Abstract: Map of northern Germany showing areas corresponding to the electorate of Hanover (also known as the electorate of Brunswick-LuÌˆneburg).
Notes: Published in the Gentlemen's magazine for January 1761.

Detached from: The gentleman's magazine, and historical chronicle. Volume XXXI : for the year M.DCC.LXI. London : Printed for D. Henry 1761. Map was originally published in the January 1761 issue, and was apparently relocated to the end of bound volumes of Volume XXXI.
Includes 2 inset maps: Dutchy of Saxon Lauwenburg Duchy of Saxe-Lauenburg -- Dutchy's of Bremen and Ferden Duchies of Bremen and Verden.
